> We love a good Plant Based Massaman Meatball Curry and this deliciously simple, 
> chef-curated recipe doesn't disappoint. Time to bust out the pots and pans!

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the rice. When boiling, add the @long grain rice{150%g} and simmer until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @green beans{80%g} then chop into thirds. Trim the @spring onion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #frying pan{} on a medium high heat. When hot, add the @Linda McCartney vegetarian meatballs{8}. Fry the balls turning frequently until golden and starting to brown all over, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the balls are browned, add the chopped onion and green beans. Cook until tender, stirring frequently, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @Massaman curry paste{50%g}, cook stirring frequently for ~{1%minute}. Add the @coconut milk{200%ml} and stir together. Bring to a boil, season with salt and pepper and simmer until the beans are tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of water to loosen if you need to. Once cooked, taste and season with salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Share the rice between your bowls. Top with the curry. Sprinkle over the spring onion and chopped peanuts. Enjoy!